<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Daemon • Easy Setup Guide</title>
    <style>
        @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&amp;family=Space+Grotesk:wght@500;600&amp;display=swap');

        :root {
            --bg: #0f172a;
            --card: #1e2937;
            --text: #e2e8f0;
            --accent: #3b82f6;
        }

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', system_ui, sans-serif;
            max-width: 860px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: var(--bg);
            color: var(--text);
            line-height: 1.75;
        }

        h1, h2, h3 {
            font-family: 'Space Grotesk', system_ui, sans-serif;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
        }

        .header h1 {
            font-size: 2.75rem;
            margin: 0;
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, #3b82f6, #60a5fa);
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        }

        .card {
            background: var(--card);
            border-radius: 16px;
            padding: 26px 28px;
            margin-bottom: 26px;
            border: 1px solid #334155;
        }

        .section-title {
            font-size: 1.45rem;
            margin: 0 0 18px 0;
            color: #f1f5f9;
        }

        .hotkey {
            background: #0f172a;
            color: #60a5fa;
            padding: 5px 13px;
            border-radius: 7px;
            font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            border: 1px solid #334155;
        }

        .step {
            display: flex;
            gap: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
            align-items: flex-start;
        }

        .step-number {
            background: #3b82f6;
            color: white;
            width: 28px;
            height: 28px;
            border-radius: 9999px;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            font-weight: 800;
            flex-shrink: 0;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        .terminal-box {
            background: #0f172a;
            color: #60a5fa;
            padding: 15px 18px;
            border-radius: 11px;
            font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;
            font-size: 0.92rem;
            margin: 12px 0;
            border: 1px solid #334155;
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }

        .copy-btn {
            background: #334155;
            color: #94a3b8;
            border: none;
            padding: 9px 18px;
            border-radius: 9px;
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        .copy-btn:hover {
            background: #475569;
            color: white;
        }

        .success-box {
            background: #052e16;
            border-left: 5px solid #22c55e;
            padding: 16px 20px;
            border-radius: 11px;
            margin: 16px 0;
        }

        .warning-box {
            background: #451a03;
            border-left: 5px solid #eab308;
            padding: 16px 20px;
            border-radius: 11px;
            margin: 16px 0;
        }

        .critical-box {
            background: #450a0a;
            border: 2px solid #ef4444;
            padding: 18px 22px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            margin: 18px 0;
        }

        .highlight {
            background: #1e3a8a;
            border: 2px solid #3b82f6;
            padding: 18px 22px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            margin: 18px 0;
        }

        ul {
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        li {
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        @media (max-width: 600px) {
            body {
                padding: 12px;
                margin: 20px auto;
            }
            .card {
                padding: 20px 18px;
            }
            .header h1 {
                font-size: 2.3rem;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="header">
        <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; gap:12px; margin-bottom:6px;">
            <div style="width:54px; height:54px; background:#3b82f6; border-radius:14px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;">
                <span style="color:white; font-size:30px; font-weight:800;">D</span>
            </div>
            <h1 style="margin:0; font-size:2.7rem;">Daemon</h1>
        </div>
        <p style="color:#64748b; margin-top:2px; font-size:1.15rem;">Simple • Stealthy • Powerful</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Download & Prepare -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title">1. Download and Prepare Daemon</h2>
        
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div>Download the compiled <strong>Daemon</strong> file.</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div>Move the <strong>Daemon</strong> file to your <strong>Desktop</strong>.</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div>Make sure the file name is exactly <strong>Daemon</strong> (no extra text).</div>
        </div>

        <div class="warning-box">
            <strong>If Daemon won't open:</strong><br>
            Open Terminal on your Mac and paste this command:
            <div class="terminal-box" id="fix">xattr -cr \~/Desktop/Daemon</div>
            <button onclick="copyToClipboard('fix')" class="copy-btn">📋 Copy</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 2. Give Permissions -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title">2. Give Daemon Permissions</h2>
        <p>Daemon needs special permissions to capture your screen and control the mouse.</p>

        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div>Click the Apple menu () → <strong>System Settings</strong>.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div>Click <strong>Privacy &amp; Security</strong> in the sidebar.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div>Scroll down and click <strong>Accessibility</strong>.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">4</div>
            <div>Click the <strong>+</strong> button and add the <strong>Daemon</strong> file from your Desktop.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">5</div>
            <div>Also add <strong>Terminal</strong> in the same list.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="success-box">
            These permissions are required for Daemon to work.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 3. Get API Key + Add Credit -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title">3. Get Your Gemini API Key + Add Credit</h2>
        
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div>Go to: <a href="https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey" target="_blank">Google AI Studio API Keys</a></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div>Click <strong>Create API Key</strong> and copy the key.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div>Open Daemon and press <span class="hotkey">Ctrl + E</span> to open Settings.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">4</div>
            <div>Paste the API key into the field.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">5</div>
            <div><strong>Click the Save button</strong> in Settings.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="highlight">
            <strong>Important:</strong> You need to add at least <strong>$10 USD</strong> of credit to your Gemini API account for it to work properly during exams.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 4. Launch Daemon -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title">4. Launch Daemon and Spoof VM</h2>
        
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div>Open the <strong>Daemon</strong> file from your Desktop.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div>Press <span class="hotkey">Ctrl + E</span> to open Settings.</div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="highlight">
            <strong>Very Important:</strong><br>
            In Settings, click the <strong>Spoof VM</strong> button.<br>
            This helps Daemon stay hidden while running on top of Parallels.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 5. Parallels + Windows 11 -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title">5. Set Up Parallels + Windows 11</h2>
        <p>You will run <strong>Bluebook</strong> inside Windows 11. Daemon runs on your Mac.</p>

        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div>Watch this video and install Parallels Desktop + Windows 11:<br>
                <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3v8Qv5vNq8k" target="_blank">→ Watch Installation Video</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div>Inside the Windows 11 virtual machine, install <strong>Bluebook</strong>.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="success-box">
            <strong>Remember:</strong> Bluebook runs inside Windows 11.<br>
            Daemon runs on your Mac (on top of Parallels).
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 6. Run auto.ps1 inside VM (UPDATED WITH CRITICAL WARNING) -->
    <div class="card" style="border: 2px solid #ef4444;">
        <h2 class="section-title">6. Run auto.ps1 Inside Windows 11 VM</h2>
        <p><strong>Do these steps inside your Windows 11 virtual machine.</strong></p>

        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div>Download <strong>auto.ps1</strong> and save it to the Desktop inside Windows 11:<br>
                <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1H3MIVGva0HTylTNZwaM39SCajHs9wuaG/view?usp=drivesdk" target="_blank">Download auto.ps1</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div>Click the Windows search bar at the bottom and type <strong>PowerShell</strong>.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div>Right-click on <strong>Windows PowerShell</strong> and choose <strong>Run as administrator</strong>.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">4</div>
            <div>First, paste this command and press Enter:</div>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-box" id="policy">Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force</div>
        <button onclick="copyToClipboard('policy')" class="copy-btn">📋 Copy</button>

        <div class="step" style="margin-top:20px;">
            <div class="step-number">5</div>
            <div>Then paste these two lines one after another:</div>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-box" id="auto">cd "C:\Mac\Home\Desktop"
.\auto.ps1</div>
        <button onclick="copyToClipboard('auto')" class="copy-btn">📋 Copy Both Lines</button>

        <!-- CRITICAL WARNING -->
        <div class="critical-box">
            <strong>⚠️ CRITICAL WARNING — READ CAREFULLY</strong><br><br>
            You <strong>must run auto.ps1 again every time you restart</strong> the Windows 11 virtual machine.<br><br>
            The spoofing does <strong>not</strong> survive a full reboot. If you restart the VM without running this script again, Bluebook may detect the virtual machine.
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 7. How Daemon Works -->
    <div class="card">
        <h2 class="section-title">7. How Daemon Works</h2>
        
        <p><strong>Daemon runs on your Mac</strong>, on top of Parallels. It can see your screen inside the Windows 11 virtual machine during Bluebook exams.</p>

        <h3>The Floating Button</h3>
        <p>When you open Daemon, a small white button appears on your screen. You can drag it anywhere with your mouse. Click it at any time to instantly capture the screen and get the AI answer.</p>

        <h3>Hotkeys</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="hotkey">Cmd + E</span> — Capture screen + get AI answer</li>
            <li><span class="hotkey">Cmd + S</span> — Screenshot to clipboard (paste with Cmd + V)</li>
            <li><span class="hotkey">Cmd + T</span> — Open floating browser</li>
            <li><span class="hotkey">Cmd + H</span> — Hide / Show HUD + floating button</li>
            <li><span class="hotkey">Ctrl + E</span> — Open Settings</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- 8. Reset Parallels Trial -->
    <div class="card" style="border: 2px solid #22c55e;">
        <h2 class="section-title" style="color:#4ade80;">8. Reset Parallels Free Trial</h2>
        <p>When your Parallels trial is ending, run this command in <strong>Terminal on your Mac</strong>:</p>

        <div class="terminal-box" id="reset">
sudo bash -c '
pkill -9 -f "Parallels Desktop" || true
pkill -9 prl_client_app || true
pkill -9 prl_disp_service || true
rm -f /private/var/root/Library/Preferences/com.parallels.desktop.plist /Library/Preferences/Parallels/licenses.xml 2>/dev/null || true
rm -rf \~/Library/Preferences/com.parallels.* \~/Library/Preferences/Parallels* "$HOME/Library/Application Support/Parallels" "$HOME/Library/Caches/Parallels" /Library/Preferences/com.parallels.* /Library/Preferences/Parallels* "/Library/Application Support/Parallels" 2>/dev/null || true
launchctl stop com.parallels.desktop.launchdaemon 2>/dev/null || true
launchctl start com.parallels.desktop.launchdaemon 2>/dev/null || true
echo "✅ Reset complete. Fully quit Parallels, reboot your Mac, then launch it again."
'
        </div>
        <button onclick="copyToClipboard('reset')" class="copy-btn">📋 Copy Reset Command</button>

        <div class="success-box" style="margin-top:14px;">
            After running: Fully quit Parallels → <strong>Reboot your Mac</strong> → Open Parallels again.
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="warning-box">
        <strong>Final Reminder:</strong><br><br>
        • Run <strong>Bluebook</strong> inside the Windows 11 virtual machine.<br>
        • Run <strong>Daemon</strong> on your Mac (on top of Parallels).<br>
        • Use <span class="hotkey">Cmd + E</span> or the floating button to get answers.<br>
        • <strong>Run auto.ps1 again every time you restart the VM.</strong>
    </div>

    <script>
        function copyToClipboard(elementId) {
            const element = document.getElementById(elementId);
            const text = element.innerText.trim();
            
            navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
                const btns = document.querySelectorAll('.copy-btn');
                btns.forEach(btn => {
                    if (btn.getAttribute('onclick') && btn.getAttribute('onclick').includes(elementId)) {
                        const original = btn.innerHTML;
                        btn.innerHTML = '✅ Copied!';
                        setTimeout(() => { btn.innerHTML = original; }, 1500);
                    }
                });
            });
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>